.TH "hfi1_make_ruc_header_9B" 9 "hfi1_make_ruc_header_9B" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hfi1_make_ruc_header_9B \- build a 9B header
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hfi1_make_ruc_header_9B
.BI "(struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "struct ib_other_headers *ohdr "  ","
.BI "u32 bth0 "  ","
.BI "u32 bth1 "  ","
.BI "u32 bth2 "  ","
.BI "int middle "  ","
.BI "struct hfi1_pkt_state *ps "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qp" 12
the queue pair
.IP "ohdr" 12
a pointer to the destination header memory
.IP "bth0" 12
bth0 passed in from the RC/UC builder
.IP "bth1" 12
bth1 passed in from the RC/UC builder
.IP "bth2" 12
bth2 passed in from the RC/UC builder
.IP "middle" 12
non zero implies indicates ahg "could" be used
.IP "ps" 12
the current packet state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine may disarm ahg under these situations:
- packet needs a GRH
- BECN needed
- migration state not IB_MIG_MIGRATED
